It is the last week of September and here is a list of exciting events to make the month a memorable one. Lights Camera Africa!! Film Festival The Lights Camera Film festival themed ‘Who do you think you are’ will be hosted by Lola Akindoju. It will be held from 28 to 30th September 2018. It will be kicked off with a cocktail followed by film screenings with the premiere of Ema Edosio’ s Film Kasala.
In addition, there will be special musical performances and other exciting activities. Belvedere Vodka With Laolu Concept Tour Belvedere Vodka, the original super premium vodka that stands for taste and character, is excited to announce its global partnership with the award-winning visual artist, musician, and activist Laolu Senbanjo.
The highly-acclaimed visual artist has designed a stunning limited-edition bottle to be unveiled during a series of events in Nigeria this September.
On Friday 28 September, there will be a luxury shopping experience to be capped with a fashion soiree. Africa Fashion Season Collection in Paris Lagos, Nigeria – Lagos Fashion Week in collaboration with SheTrades and NEPC is pleased to announce the new season collection viewing at Gallery Sakura, Paris from the 28th of September to the 3rd of October 2018.
The viewing will feature designers: A.A.K.S, Afrodesiac, Aprelle Duany, Anyango Mpinga, Christie Brown, Eclectic Chique, Grey, Iamisigo, Nkwo, Maki Oh, Style Temple, Tilayo and Zashadu. Lords of The Ribs Comedy Festival <img class="aligncenter wp-image-750944 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth.jpeg" alt="" width="863" height="1080" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth.jpeg 863w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth-478x598.jpeg 478w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth-445x557.jpeg 445w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth-192x240.jpeg 192w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth-384x480.jpeg 384w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Basket-mouth-479x600.jpeg 479w" sizes="(max-width: 863px) 100vw, 863px" /> The 2018 edition of ‘Lord of the ribs’ festival will be held from 28 to 30 September with Basket mouth as host. The show will feature some to the finest comedians and artiste and promises to be a rib-cracking affair. Venue:Eko Hotel Convention centre Lagos. Date:28-30 September 2018 Time: 6pm